tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating possible impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and presence of ketones and bilirubin, suggesting renal tubular dysfunction and possible nephrotic or diabetic nephropathy. No evidence of urinary tract infection is seen. Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
